This is how people I met people from TikTok who changed my life for the better at a time when I felt alone with no meaningful relationships. In 2018 I started posting to TikTok to share my art and journey with more people and to document my journey from AZ to NYC. I got serious about content creation in 2020 when I was receiving unemployment and didn’t have to worry about my basic needs since we were being payed $700 a week. 

During this time I was invited to join multiple artists clubs where we discussed our current projects, struggles, and collaborations. During this time I met so many amazing artists from all over the world but my friend Yen revealed to me that we can make our dreams reality. We had our first gallery exhibition in Manhattan, which is something I never knew would be possible when I started my journey as an artist.

I first saw William Beteet’s face on my foryou page talking about philosophy and his message resonated with my life experience. I saw he was also living in Brooklyn so I hit him up to hang at mgy studio. We hit it off immediately and our energy’s complimented each other. William inspires me to be the best version of myself because he believes in me even when I have moments of self doubt. 

William invited me to a creator event in LA where I met Vijay and Adi both amazingly talented creators who then invited me to a dinner party in NYC. At this dinner party I met my friend Anant who is a co-founder at verci. I was then invited to be apart of season 0 and now I’m working in the financial district as a full time artist. Im curating the next group exhibition “Reality in bloom” at verci 

Like & follow to stay up to date on upcoming events 
Thank you for following my journey and supporting my dreams.

Experience the digital renaissance with 444 AI-generated artworks by @cafesamosablue and @michael.cota. These one-of-a-kind pieces represent a new era in art, where human creativity meets the boundless possibilities of technology.

Getting outside of my comfort zone has always been an important part of my artistic journey. Whether it's trying a new medium or collaborating with people from different industries, I believe that pushing myself to try new things is essential to growth and development as an artist. It can be intimidating to take risks and to put myself out there, but the rewards of stepping out of my comfort zone are always worth it.

Staying consistent and dedicated to my art has also been key to my success. It can be easy to get sidetracked or to lose motivation, but I have found that setting aside dedicated time for my work and being disciplined in my approach has helped me to stay focused and to bring my ideas to fruition. Seeing my artwork come to life is always such a satisfying and rewarding experience, and it's what keeps me motivated to continue creating.
Thankful for 2022🎁🎊❤️‍🔥

Attention art lovers! I’m thrilled to invite you to the Beyond Art Gala, showcasing my latest works. This will be a day to celebrate art and its power to evoke emotions, provoke thought, and bring people together. This one-day event will take place on February 25th from 12pm to 9pm at 23 Warren St, New York, NY 10007.

I pour my soul into every piece I create and I can't wait to share my latest creations with you. From vibrant colors to intricate details, my works will take you on a journey beyond the ordinary and into the realm of the extraordinary.

At the Beyond Art Gala, you'll have the opportunity to see my art up close and personal, and to engage with me in a discussion about my creative process. I am passionate about sharing my art and the stories behind it, and I look forward to hearing your perspectives and thoughts.

Let's delve into the world of art together and explore what lies beyond. I can't wait to see you there!

Hey everyone, I'm back from an incredible adventure in Japan, I'm excited to continue my work and experiencing extreme gratitude! I had the incredible opportunity to help my friend @cafesamosablue host the first international tricking gathering in Aichi, which was an unforgettable experience. I met so many incredibly talented people, saw some legendary performances, and made memories that will last a lifetime.

While I was in Japan, I also had the opportunity to discover some new art residencies and immerse myself in the vibrant art scene there. I was blown away by the creativity and innovation I saw, and I'm feeling so inspired to learn new technologies and incorporate them into my own work.

I can't express enough gratitude to @cafesamosablue for inviting me to be a part of this adventure. It was an incredible opportunity to learn and grow, and I'm so grateful for the chance to be a part of it.

Now that I'm back home, I'm excited to focus on my next big project: Beyond Art Gala happening on February 25th. I've been hard at work creating a new body of work, and I can't wait to share it with all of you.
Thank you for your support, and I can't wait to see you at the exhibition! Click the link in my bio to RSVP🎟🎨🌟

We interact with so many different digital realities on a daily basis and our every action is being tracked to profit off of the things that we unconsciously desire. Are the desires our own or have we been following someone else’s plan for our life? My new series of paintings will express my thoughts on this subject.

Digital realities are technologies that fuse the physical and digital worlds into one machine-readable reality. They include virtual reality (VR), augmented reality (AR) and mixed reality (MR), which can be used together to create extended reality (XR).

But what are the implications of these technologies for our privacy, identity and autonomy? How do they affect our perception of reality and our sense of self? How do they influence our choices and preferences? And who controls the data that is generated by these technologies?

These are some of the questions that I explore in my new series of paintings, titled “Digital Dilemmas”. In these paintings, I use various techniques and symbols to represent the contrast and conflict between the physical and digital realities, and the challenges and opportunities that they pose for us as individuals and as a society.

These new technologies create ethical dilemmas and risks for the everyone’s privacy, security and autonomy, as they may not be aware of who or what is in control of these digital realities.

These are just some examples of how I express my thoughts on digital realities in my paintings. I hope you enjoyed this video and found it interesting. If you did, please like and follow for more. And if you want to see my paintings in person, please visit my website for more information on where and when they will be exhibited. Thank you for watching and see you next time.

“Breaking Through Creative Blocks: 4 Essential Techniques”

✅ Technique 1: Mindfulness and meditation. Take a moment to breathe, quiet your mind, and be present. By practicing mindfulness and meditation, you can clear away distractions and reconnect with your inner creativity.

✅ Technique 2: Exploring new mediums. Step out of your comfort zone and try something different. Experiment with various artistic mediums to stimulate your creativity and discover fresh perspectives.

✅ Technique 3: Collaborating with peers. Engage with fellow creatives. Share your ideas, seek feedback, and collaborate on projects. The collective energy and diverse perspectives can help reignite your creative spark.

✅ Technique 4: Change you surroundings. Changing your surroundings is beneficial for the creative process because it offers fresh perspectives and breaks you away from your familiur environment. New environments will engage all of your senses and trigger innovative thinking. Diversity in surroundings inspires unique ideas and approaches. Some examples would inclued nature, art shows, museums, and concerts.

So, whether it’s through mindfulness, exploring new mediums, collaborating with peers, or embracing playfulness, these techniques can help you push through creative blocks and unlock your full creative potential.🚀

Remember, creativity is within you, waiting to be unleashed. Break through those barriers, embrace your uniqueness, and let your creativity inspire others.💫
